MG_229_231_TETRAMER: belongs to class Ib enzymes (https://pubs.acs.org/doi/10.1021/bi981380s). The interaction between MG_230_MONOMER (NrdI) and Ribonucleotide Reductase holoenzyme (MG_229_231_TETRAMER) are not fully understood. It has been hypothesized that the holoenzyme for transitioning to its oxidized form might undergo to complex disassembling; MG_229 (NrdF) interacts with MG_230 (NrdI) and subsequently reassembles into the holoenzyme (https://pubs.acs.org/doi/10.1021/cb400757h; https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6754363/). Alternatively it was suggested that NrdI binding would not disturb the holoenzyme assembly (https://pubs.acs.org/doi/abs/10.1021/bi200348q). In this model we will represent the hypotesis of the holoenzyme assembled as a heterotetramer without MG_230.

Pyruvate dehydrogenase is a multienzyme complex composed by three subunits: E1-alpha (MG_274); E1-beta(MG_273); E2 (MG_272) and E3 (MG_271). In gram positive bacteria the 60-meric core (E2) exhibits icosahedral symmetry. Many structures of E2 from various organisms have been solved so far but none of them covered the entire E2 sequence. The missing domain of E2 structures is the N-term domain; an extremely flexible part of the enzyme; whose mobility is essential for the functioning of the whole enzyme complex. The N-term extends outwards from the 60-meric core and engages non-covalent binding with E1 and E3 subunits that decorate the outer shell of pyruvate dehydrogenase. Typically; a complex is made of 42-48 E1 tetramers; 6-12 E3 dimers and one 60-mer E2. Although; the stoichiometry of E1 and E3 is likely to vary from one complex to the other and also among different organisms. The overall complex is approximately 450A across; with an annular gap between the inner and the outer shell of approximately 70A. In the WC model; MG_271_272_273_274_192MER coordinates come from a cryoEM structure reconstruction (10.1093/emboj/cdf574; 10.1074/jbc.M504363200). The model comprises 60E2 and 60E3; although the interpretation of such model is that E3 monomers represent the two most likely location of a given E3 at any given time. Overall; the shape and the volume of this 3D model resemble the naive assembly of PDH.

MG_451 gene product (elongation factor Tu; EF-Tu) forms a monomer according to https://www.uniprot.org/. EF-tu-GDP binds transiently MG_433 gene product (Elongation factor Ts); the binding induces the exchange of GDP to GTP. EF-Tu promotes the binding of aminoacyl-tRNA to the ribosome. MG_433 remains bound to the aminoacyl-tRNA-EF-Tu-GTP  complex up to the GTP hydrolysis stage on the ribosome.

MG experimentally solved structure: 2JMP (partial coverage). MG_469_MONOMER (DnaA) binds DnaA-boxes to form a complex initiating chromosomal DNA replication. It assembles into a multimeric nucleoprotein complex. Structural homolog 2HCB/3R8F was selected to structurally represent MG DnaA as it shows the highest coverage among homologous stuctures and a reasonable biological assembly. A speculative model provided by Prof. Berger was used to represent different oligomeric conformations of DnaA bound to dsDNA in presence of ADP or ATP (DOI: 10.1038/nsmb1115; DOI: 10.1038/nature10455). The helical assembly was retrieved from the crystal symmetry of DnaA from Aquifex aeolicus (PDBid 2HCB). Replication initiation on WC-MG model was derived from Messer reconstruction (https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/12413665/).
